{{Infobox song contest | name = Melodifestivalen | year = 1977 | theme = | logo = | final = 26 February 1977 | presenters = [[Ulf Elfving]] | winner = | vote = Regional juries | host = "[[Beatles (song)|Beatles]]" by [[Forbes (band)|Forbes]] | venue = [[Cirkus (Stockholm)|Cirkus]], [[Stockholm]] | entries = | interval = | opening = }}
'''[[Melodifestivalen]] 1977''' was the selection for the 17th song to represent [[Sweden]] at the [[Eurovision Song Contest]]. Sweden did not participate in the [[Eurovision Song Contest 1976]] due to demonstrations against commercial music. It was the 16th time that this system of picking a song had been used. 965 songs were submitted to [[Sveriges Television|SVT]] for the competition. The final was broadcast on [[SVT1|TV1]] but was not broadcast on radio.
