{{Orphan|date=October 2015}}

'''Pakbugs''' was a [[Pakistan]]i-based [[crime forum]] and security releases updates, offering discussion of [[Hacker (computer security)|hacking]], [[credit card fraud]], [[phishing]] and other forms of [[computer crime]]; as well as [[trading]] in [[malware]], bank login details and stolen [[credit card]] numbers.<ref name="reg">https://www.theregister.co.uk/2010/07/13/pakbugs_crackdown/</ref> The forum was shut down by Pakistani [[Federal Investigation Agency]] after raids in 2010, in which five individuals were arrested, with the alleged founder suspected to remain at large in [[Riyadh]].<ref name="reg"/><ref>{{cite web|author1=Carvell, Andy|title=Pakistan hacker forum Pakbugs busted|url=http://www.geek.com/news/pakistan-hacker-forum-pakbugs-busted-1269490/|website=geek.com|publisher=Ziff Davis|accessdate=2 November 2015|format=|date=13 July 2010}}</ref>

In addition to being a crime forum, ''PAKbugs'' was also the nomenclature of a group, used by individuals on numerous occasions to claim responsibility and attribution for defacement of several high-profile Web sites.<ref>{{cite web|author1=Constantin, Lucian|title=Notorious Website Defacers Arrested in Pakistan|url=http://news.softpedia.com/news/Notorious-Website-Defacers-Arrested-in-Pakistan-147087.shtml|website=Softpedia|accessdate=2 November 2015|date=12 July 2010}}</ref>

Also, the forum offered resources and courses to pen-testing, programming and a lot of IT subjects, from beginner to advanced.
A lot of users was registered to learn about programming, security, software engineering.

