{{Multiple issues| {{Notability|Events|date=June 2018}} {{third-party|date=June 2018}} {{primary sources|date=June 2018}} }} {{Infobox Convention | name = Quinni-Con | image = [[Image:Quinni-Con logo.jpg|175px]] | caption = The official Quinni-Con 2013 logo | status = Defunct | genre = [[Anime]], [[Manga]], Pop culture, Multi-genre | venue = [[Quinnipiac University#Campuses|Quinnipiac University York Hill Campus, Rocky Top Student Center]] | location = [[Hamden, Connecticut]] | country = United States | first = 2012 | last = 2014 | organizer = Quinnipiac University Anime Club | filing = | attendance = 1087 in 2014{{cn|date=January 2016}} | website = http://www.quinni-con.com/ }} '''Quinni-Con''' was an annual two-day [[anime]] [[fan convention]] held during March or April at the Rocky Top Student Center on the [[Quinnipiac University#Campuses|Quinnipiac University York Hill Campus]] in [[Hamden, Connecticut]]. The convention featured a number of events which included a tea café, video programming rooms, a dealers' alley (combination artists' and vendors' alley), guest speakers, a [[video game]] room, and a dance.<ref name="FAQ">{{cite web|title=Quinni-Con FAQ|url=http://quinni-con.com/FAQ.html|accessdate=March 4, 2013}}</ref><ref name="AC2012"/> Quinni-Con was created and run by the Quinnipiac University Anime Club, and the name of the event is derived from the school.
==History== The first Quinni-Con was held in 2012. The Quinnipiac Anime Club is responsible for conceptualizing, coordinating, and running the convention.<ref name="quadnews">{{cite web|title=Quinni-Con Draws over 400 to Quinnipiac|url=http://www.quadnews.net/news/quinni-con-draws-over-400-to-quinnipiac-1.2737323#.UWtStMprg_d|last=Scinto|first=Rich|date=April 30, 2012|accessdate=April 14, 2013}}</ref> The event has not charged for admittance or hospitality,<ref name="quchronicle">{{cite web|title=Quinni-Con Draws over 400 to Quinnipiac|url=http://www.quchronicle.com/2012/05/anime-club-hosts-first-quinni-con-convention/|last=Wagner|first=Anna|date=May 2, 2012|accessdate=April 14, 2013}}</ref> instead collecting donations for [[Child's Play (charity)|Child's Play]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Child's Play Charity Events Calendar: Events Calendar Quinni-Con 2012|url=http://childsplaycharity.org/events/post/quinni-con|accessdate=April 14, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Child's Play Charity Events Calendar: Events Calendar Quinni-Con 2013|url=http://www.childsplaycharity.org/events/post/quinni-con1|accessdate=April 14, 2013}}</ref> The 2015 convention was cancelled due to problems including location availability.<ref name="AC2015">{{cite web | title=Quinni-Con 2015 Information | url=https://animecons.com/events/info/5569/quinni-con-2015 | publisher = AnimeCons.com | accessdate=February 1, 2015}}</ref> A larger venue was announced for 2016's convention - the CoCo Key Water Resort/Hotel Convention Center in [[Waterbury, Connecticut|Waterbury, CT]].<ref name="AC2016">{{cite web | title=Quinni-Con 2016 Information | url=https://animecons.com/events/info/6822/quinni-con-2016 | publisher = AnimeCons.com | accessdate=January 18, 2016}}</ref> However, the convention that year was cancelled as well six days before it was scheduled to be held, citing planning issues and the looming closure of the venue.<ref name="2016 cancellation">{{cite web|title=4/24 – Unfortunate News|url=http://quinni-con.com/?p=523|accessdate=April 25, 2016}}</ref>
===Event History=== {| class="wikitable" width="75%" ! Date !! Location !! Atten. !! Guests |- {{Convention list | date = April 28–29, 2012 | venue = Quinnipiac University York Hill Campus, Rocky Top Student Center | location = [[Hamden, Connecticut]] | attendance = 520{{cn|date=January 2016}} | guests = Lisle Wilkerson, Jessi Nowack, Michael Hecht,<ref name="AC2012">{{cite web | title=Quinni-Con 2012 Information | url=https://animecons.com/events/info/2797/quinni-con-2012 | publisher = AnimeCons.com | accessdate=March 4, 2013}}</ref><ref name="Special Guests 2012">{{cite web|title=2012 Special Guests|url=http://quinni-con.com/SpecialGuests2012.html|accessdate=October 10, 2013}}</ref> Savan Gupta, Steam-Funk. }} {{Convention list | date = April 20–21, 2013 | venue = Quinnipiac University York Hill Campus, Rocky Top Student Center | location = [[Hamden, Connecticut]] | attendance = 700 (estimated) | guests = [[Chris Cason]], Jessi Nowack, Michael Hecht, The [[501st Legion]], The Asterplace, Savan Gupta, Steam-Funk.<ref name="Special Guests 2013">{{cite web|title=2013 Special Guests|url=http://quinni-con.com/SpecialGuests2013.html|accessdate=October 10, 2013}}</ref><ref name="AC2013">{{cite web | title= Quinni-Con 2013 Information | url= https://animecons.com/events/info/3794/quinni-con-2013 | publisher = AnimeCons.com | accessdate= March 4, 2013}}</ref> }} {{Convention list | date = March 1–2, 2014 | venue = Quinnipiac University York Hill Campus, Rocky Top Student Center | location = [[Hamden, Connecticut]] | attendance = 1087{{cn|date=January 2016}} | guests = [[Mike Pollock (voice actor)|Mike Pollock]], [[Chris Patton]], Jessi Nowack, Michael Hecht, Jerry Pakalinsky, Nick Lizzo, Rusty Gilligan, Jim Taylor, Crunk Witch.<ref name="Special Guests 2014">{{cite web|title=2014 Special Guests|url=http://quinni-con.com/SpecialGuests.html|accessdate=October 11, 2013}}</ref><ref name="AC2014">{{cite web | title= Quinni-Con 2014 Information | url= https://animecons.com/events/info/4406/quinni-con-2014 | publisher = AnimeCons.com | accessdate= October 16, 2018}}</ref> }} |}
