{{Notability|date=March 2009}}
The '''Ruta del Sol''' ({{lang-en|Route of the Sun}}) is an [[amateur]] [[Auto racing|motor race]] for [[Charitable organization|charity]] using a [[Volkswagen Beetle|VW Beetle]] to race from [[Quito]], [[Ecuador]] to [[Rio de Janeiro|Rio]], [[Brazil]], a distance of some 7000 km.
In 2009 the event is changing its name and format. The details have not yet been released by the organisers.
The Ruta Del Sol, organised by the Adventurists, took place in February 2008. It took the teams into the wilds of [[Latin America]] through thousands of miles of hardcore [[jungle]]s and [[rainforest]], the [[Andes]], awful roads, complete absence of roads and [[Tropics|tropical]] weather. Each team taking part has to provide their own [[Volkswagen Beetle|VW Beetle]] and to raise a minimum amount for charity.
[[Fundecruz]] was the official charity of the February 2008 Ruta del Sol.<ref>{{cite news | url=http://ruta.theadventurists.com/index.php?page=charities | title=Official charity for the Ruta | publisher=ruta.theadventurists.com | accessdate=2008-01-03}}</ref><ref>{{cite news | date=2007-12-20 | url=http://www.readingfc.premiumtv.co.uk/page/NewsDetail/0,,10306~1193203,00.html | title=Help Ulises with his charity work | publisher=readingfc.co.uk | accessdate=2008-01-03 | deadurl=yes | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080103071234/http://www.readingfc.premiumtv.co.uk/page/NewsDetail/0,,10306~1193203,00.html | archivedate=2008-01-03 | df= }}</ref>
